  <ul>
    <li>My desk is a cheap 47" Tresanti standing desk from Costco.</li>
    <li>For a chair I use a Autonomus MayoChair.</li>
    <li>
      For monitors, I use two <a href="https://amzn.to/3vjojRL" target="_blank"
        >Samsung 34 inch S7 Monitors</a
      >.
    </li>
    <li>
      My keyboard is a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/KINESIS-Advantage360-Professional-Ergonomic-Keyboard/dp/B0BCHMGZMD/ref=sr_1_1?crid=522W4OVV0R4J&dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.wNQMIbPMWY1CxBfyGZUIgYdsmeSbmcQLyzSuqbtRmtcpnTze_BEjh8NVWUkOtkGo3EftqVLb125OuylGfbNY8TwYXVOi1xF3gIM41hvIFYzHZ-dyK8wtYlqeDErW1aN6Axz9LlPrz0VomSVWOzpnaL2nQRKl0TjrZ0JiEDWv4MAHJl1Yx4NhWBAWlcUXEE7QyB5pmjLqhWYcJk59GVgBtHOZPlUkhd5dsOipnUlFnnM.9Sns1faWRt7ZnFYTaraPkBYPp4-WZoS5Z1IJsTvhytE&dib_tag=se&keywords=kinesis+advantage+360&qid=1732165928&sprefix=kinesis+a%2Caps%2C334&sr=8-1" target="_blank"
        >Kinesis Advantage 360</a
      > with Brown switches.
    </li>
    <li>
      I use a <a href="https://amzn.to/48CKz7E" target="_blank"
        >Logitech G502 Hero</a
      > Mouse.
    </li>
    <li>
      As desk speakers I use a pair of vintage bookshelf speakers along with a 
      vintage Harmon/Kardon AVR 10 receiver.
    </li>
    <li>
      For headphones I use a pair of <a
